--------------------------------------------------
ARCHITECTURE RULES
--------------------------------------------------

- Business logic goes in /services.
- AI logic goes in /lib/ai.
- Database access goes in /lib/db.
- UI components must never call external APIs directly.
- Use Server Actions for mutations.
- Prefer Server Components.
- Client Components only when necessary.

--------------------------------------------------
RESPONSIVE DESIGN (MANDATORY)
--------------------------------------------------

The app MUST be fully responsive and mobile-first.

Rules:
- Always design mobile-first.
- Use Tailwind responsive utilities (sm, md, lg, xl).
- Never hardcode widths unless necessary.
- Use max-width containers with proper padding.
- Ensure layout works on:
  - Mobile (320px+)
  - Tablet
  - Desktop
  - Large screens

--------------------------------------------------
NAVBAR REQUIREMENTS (STRICT)
--------------------------------------------------

The Navbar must be:

- Fully responsive
- Collapsible on mobile (hamburger menu)
- Smooth animated open/close
- Accessible (keyboard navigable)
- Sticky or fixed (clean SaaS style)
- Proper spacing and alignment
- No layout breaking on small screens
- Support auth state (logged in / logged out)
- No UI shift when resizing

On mobile:
- Use slide-in or dropdown menu
- Close on route change
- Prevent background scroll when open

--------------------------------------------------
UI/UX STANDARDS
--------------------------------------------------

- Clean SaaS minimal design
- Modern spacing system
- Consistent typography scale
- Clear visual hierarchy
- Smooth transitions
- Subtle hover effects
- Accessible contrast ratios
- Use semantic HTML

No ugly default layouts.

--------------------------------------------------
INTERVIEW LIVE MODE (FUTURE AGENT SUPPORT)
--------------------------------------------------

Architecture must support:

- Audio streaming
- Video input
- Real-time AI streaming responses
- Persona-based interviewer behavior
- Extensible persona system (strict, aggressive, calm, technical)
- Separate AI logic from UI
- Modular interview engine

--------------------------------------------------
STATE MANAGEMENT
--------------------------------------------------

- Prefer server state.
- Avoid unnecessary global state.
- Forms must be typed.
- Avoid excessive useEffect.
- Avoid prop drilling by proper structuring.

--------------------------------------------------
PERFORMANCE
--------------------------------------------------

- Avoid unnecessary client components.
- Lazy load heavy components.
- Use dynamic imports where needed.
- Avoid large bundles.
- Optimize re-renders.

--------------------------------------------------
SCALABILITY
--------------------------------------------------

- Code as if 100k+ users will use it.
- Keep AI layer swappable.
- Keep database abstraction clean.
- Avoid tight coupling.

--------------------------------------------------
CODE QUALITY
--------------------------------------------------

- Clear naming.
- Functional components only.
- No console.log in production.
- Clean imports.
- Avoid deeply nested components.
- Keep files readable and modular.

--------------------------------------------------
OUTPUT RULES FOR CURSOR
--------------------------------------------------

When generating code:
- Always output complete files.
- Include types.
- Include proper imports.
- Follow folder structure.
